values:
I've had my three cups&nbsp;of coffee, slept an extra 20 minutes today, and haven't had breakfast yet. Here are some (early) morning thoughts.

I love the people in my life. I wish that I could spend more time with everyone and give more of myself. Except I can't. Shoot. I'm really struggling to figure out&nbsp;how to balance (ha ha!) my life right now. I've just moved to an apt&nbsp;by myself, and of course I'm worried about getting lonely, but shoot, I've had people over EVERY night. This is good, but I'm feeling the need to spend some time there - with myself...These are the times I appreciate people who can come and sit and don't&nbsp;need entertained. There are lots of people I enjoy, but&nbsp;I feel like it's rare to find people you don't have to entertain (thank you Timothy!!).&nbsp;

Balance? ELUSIVE!! Will I ever be someone who leads a balanced life? Maybe. I was talking with Jess about her life in Guate and really impressed with the balance she has found - I want that!! I think it has a lot to do with her simplifying. I want to do this, but I'm not sure how. I want to walk more, buy less, grow more (veggies), read more, write more, grow more (myself), and be more hospitible. Yikes. Tall order there friend. Oops. I have lots of those, tall orders...shoot. Can I just accept, today, my pendulum swinging self, and love&nbsp;myself where I am today? Hopefully.

Peace.&nbsp;

I moved a car full of boxes&nbsp;last night, and boy am I paying for it! Yikes! And today is quite the full&nbsp;day - work, Bellefield to print bulletins in Janet's absence, dinner (maybe), and Shane Clayborne. &nbsp;It should be interesting, but hopefully I'm able to move the rest of my stuff on friday! Who knows! Hopefully brother dearest will help me. :)

In other news, I met my upstairs neighbor! It's nice to know the people I'm living around are pretty great. I actually had coffee with Ann (Landlord) for 2 or so hours yesterday, that was pretty great!! I keep being afraid that I didn't actually tell them&nbsp;I have cats, but i know I did, cuz we joked about it. And I do love the kitchen!&nbsp;

I can't wait to get everything unpacked...my neighbor said to give myself a month - but who knows, maybe it'll go faster!
